                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/2491: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="86" xml:id="d278fn86">Transmitted through the White House Map Room,
                        where it was received at 7:40 p.m. on April 15, 1944. At this time,
                        President Roosevelt was recuperating from an attack of bronchitis at Bernard
                        Baruch’s estate in Georgetown, South Carolina.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Georgetown</hi>, S.C.</placeName>,] <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-15">15 April, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to S50325 from Stettinius, any reply thereto should have my approval
                    before being sent.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
